By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  Governor Godwin Obaseki of Edo State has discharged eighteen COVID-19 patients from the hospital. Obaseki disclosed this on his official Twitter page on Sunday. This brings the total number of discharged COVID-19 patients in Edo State to 57. His tweet read: “We have discharged 18 patients who have tested negative for #COVID19 from our isolation centres. “This brings the total number of discharged persons to 57. “ The Governor advised residents in the state to continue to observe precautionary measures and take advantage of screening centers available in 18 LGA to contain the spread of Coronavirus. “I implore all residents to take advantage of the screening centres across the 18 LGAs to know their status. Stay safe,” Obaseki added. By Nefishetu Yakubu Benin - Gov. Godwin Obaseki of Edo on Friday announced the discharge of five COVID-19 patients in the state. Obaseki, who announced this via his twitter handle said the five patients were fully recovered having tested negative twice. The governor said, “I am pleased to announce that… April 17, 2020 In "Health" By Florence Onuegbu Lagos -The Lagos State Government on Saturday discharged 22 more patients who tested negative twice to coronavirus disease. Gov. Babajide Sanwo-Olu, made the disclosure in a statement issued to newsmen, saying that the number of patients treated and discharged from the isolation centres now stands at 247.… May 3, 2020 In "Health" By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - The healthcare workers handling coronavirus (COVID-19) response in Edo state have been motivated with life insurance and special allowance by Governor Godwin Obaseki as frontliners in the fight against pandemic. The Edo Governor who disclosed this in a broadcast, said the state is… April 20, 2020 In "News"